{"type":"visualization","id":"think-time-instructions","attributes":{"title":"Think Time Instructions","visState":"{\"title\":\"Think Time Instructions\",\"type\":\"markdown\",\"params\":{\"fontSize\":12,\"openLinksInNewTab\":false,\"markdown\":\"# Think Time Analysis for Gatling\\n\\nThis dashboard shows **actionable pause values** for each request transition in your Gatling scenarios.\\n\\n## Quick Start\\n\\n1. Run `./calculate-think-times.sh` to process access logs\\n2. Review **Top Transitions Table** below for `.pause()` values\\n3. Copy values directly into your Gatling scenarios\\n\\n## What is Think Time?\\n\\n**Think time** = Time users pause between requests (reading, clicking, typing)\\n\\n**Formula**: `think_time = gap_between_requests - response_time`\\n\\n## How to Apply to Gatling\\n\\n**Option 1: Per-Transition Pauses (Recommended)**\\n```scala\\nexec(http(\\\"Get tracked entities\\\").get(\\\"/api/trackedEntities\\\"))\\n  .pause(8.3, 25.7)  // Use values from table below\\nexec(http(\\\"Get events\\\").get(\\\"/api/events\\\"))\\n  .pause(3.1, 18.4)  // Different pause for different transition\\n```\\n\\n**Option 2: Global Fallback**\\n```scala\\n.pause(globalMin, globalP95)  // Use Global Pause Values below\\n```\\n\\n## Understanding the Values\\n\\n* **Min**: Fastest users (lower bound of pause range)\\n* **Median**: Typical user behavior\\n* **P95**: Slower users (upper bound of pause range)\\n* **`.pause(min, p95)`**: Gatling randomly varies pause within this range\\n\\n## Transitions Not in Logs?\\n\\nFor request transitions not captured in your test data, use the **Global Pause Values** as a fallback.\"},\"aggs\":[]}","uiStateJSON":"{}","description":"Instructions for using transition-based think times","version":1,"kibanaSavedObjectMeta":{"searchSourceJSON":"{\"query\":{\"query\":\"\",\"language\":\"kuery\"},\"filter\":[]}"}},"references":[],"migrationVersion":{"visualization":"8.5.0"},"coreMigrationVersion":"8.5.0"}
